Durban - Two men, aged 41 and 43, have appeared in court following the murders of six people from Esigodini, just outside Pietermaritzburg, at the weekend. 
Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said Sipho Mchunu and Sthembiso "Jesus" Zondi Mbambo appeared in court on charges of murder. 

"The men were arrested by officers from the Provincial Organised Crime unit. They were remanded into custody pending further investigations," she said. 
The men are believed to have been part of a gang of four men who targeted six people. 
Mbele said six cases of murder had been opened at the Plessislaer police station on Saturday. 

“All the deceased, were murdered at Emgodini. Just after 6pm, a 43-year-old man was shot dead. Later, three men entered a shop where she shot and killed three people aged between 29 and 60. A 25-year-old woman was also shot dead at her home and a 24-year-old man was gunned down,” Mbele said. 
On Monday, MEC for Transport, Community Safety and Liaison in KwaZulu-Natal, Mxolisi Kaunda, visited the area where he instructed police to continue the search for two more suspects. 
Kaunda held a meeting with police management where they discussed plans to safeguard the area.  “Part of the plans we have developed with the police include, tracing of the two suspects implicated in the killings and to increase police visibility in the area to ensure that further killings do not occur,” he said. 

The Mercury